description: An estimated 500,000 Israelis have hit the streets in protest throughout Israel  the military after six more captives were found dead in Gaza. They had been killed in the Israeli air strikes on Gaza.
title: Mass protests in Israel as six more captives killed in Gaza air strikes

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman said on Sunday that the people in the world want the Israeli leaders to stand trial for the genocide they have been committing against Palestinians since October last year.
title: Iran says the world is seeking trial of Israeli ‘criminal leaders’

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s new foreign minister reiterated on Sunday that the Islamic Republic “backs any agreement that is accepted by Palestinians, including Hamas, for reaching a ceasefire” and creating a situation to deliver humanitarian aid to the Gaza Strip.
title: Iran reiterates it backs any truce agreement accepted by Palestinians

description: TEHRAN- A mourning ceremony for the passing of Prophet Muhammad (PBUH) and martyrdom of Imam Hassan (AS), the second Shia Imam, was held at the Islamic Center of Moscow, Russia, on Sunday.
title: Mourning ceremony for Prophet demise, Imam Hassan martyrdom anniversary held in Moscow

description: TEHRAN –  A supreme investigation committee run by the General Headquarters of the Armed Forces announced on Sunday afternoon that a "sudden thick fog" resulted in the crash of the helicopter carrying President Ebrahim Raisi and his accompanying team in the forested mountainous region of East Azarbaijan province in northwestern Iran on 19 May.
title: Thick fog blamed for President Raisi’s copter crash: investigation committee

description: The Egyptian Foreign Ministry issued a statement on Sunday strongly condemning the persistence of Israeli military violence in the West Bank, which has caused dozens of casualties and injuries in the past days, Egypt Today reported.
title: Egypt denounces persistence of Israeli violence in West Bank

description: Jordan’s Foreign Minister Ayman Safadi has called Israel’s justification for its attack in the occupied West Bank a “lie”.
title: Jordanian FM rejects Israeli justification for West Bank assault

description: PARIS – Alireza Mokhtari of Iran claimed a bronze medal in the Men's Shot Put - F53 of the 2024 Paralympic Games on Sunday.
title: Iran’s Mokhtari wins bronze at 2024 Paralympic Games

description: PARIS – Alireza Mokhtari of Iran claimed a silver medal in the Men's Shot Put - F53 of the 2024 Paralympic Games on Sunday.
title: Iran’s Mokhtari wins silver at 2024 Paralympic Games

description: The UN human rights office has issued a statement accusing Israel of “unlawful killings” and wreaking “enormous destruction” in the Jenin refugee camp, which is home to about 11,000 Palestinians.
title: Israeli siege cuts off water, power in Jenin

description: PARIS – Iran’s men’s sitting volleyball team defeated Brazil in straight sets (25-12, 25-13, 25-19) in Pool B of the 2024 Paralympic Games on Sunday.
title: 2024 Paralympics: Iran sitting volleyball down Brazil

description: Resistance fighters have killed at least two Israeli security personnel and injured another in a shooting at a checkpoint in Hebron, as Israel brought reinforcements in the occupied West Bank city of Jenin as part of its ongoing deadly raids.
title: Resistance fighters kill Israeli police forces in West Bank

description: Israel’s military has announced that its troops have recovered the bodies of six captives, including a dual US national, from a tunnel in southern Gaza, as it continued its 11-month long, deadly assault on Palestinian enclave, Al Jazeera reported on Sunday.
title: Israel finds bodies of six captives killed in air strikes on Gaza
